						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Ghritasthānēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 11: 982 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 96 sheep by Siddhavaḍavan Alambaḍa dēvaṉ of Malāḍu on the occasion of solar eclipse for burning a perpetual lamp daily with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee for the god Tirunettānattu-Mahādēva. Shepherds Perumān Vīran, Perumān Kaṇṇaṉ, Peruvaḻi Echchil and Teṟṟi Śaḍaṅgavi (Shaḍaṅgavi, a brāhmaṇa ?) took over the sheep and agreed to supply the required ghee.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. V No. 606.</p>						

						</summary>
